# Distribution of Churned customers
sns.countplot(x='Exited', data=data)

plt.title('Distribution of Exited Customers')
plt.show()

In[24]:
#Group by Geography and calculate the mean of Churned
geo_exited = data.groupby('Geography')['Exited'].mean().reset_index()
sns.barplot(x='Geography', y='Exited', data=geo_exited)
plt.title('Churn Rate by Geography')
plt.show()

In[52]:
#Import Label Encoder to encode categorical variables
from sklearn.preprocessing import LabelEncoder
In[54]:
#Initialize the encoder
label_encoder = LabelEncoder()
In[56]:
#Encode Geography and PaymentMethod
data['Geography_Encoded'] = label_encoder.fit_transform(data['Geography'])
data['CardType_Encoded'] = label_encoder.fit_transform(data['CardType'])
data['Gender_Encoded'] = label_encoder.fit_transform(data['Gender'])
In[58]:
#Drop original categorical columns
data.drop(['Geography', 'CardType','Gender'], axis=1, inplace=True)
In[60]:
#Correlation matrix
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 8))
sns.heatmap(data.corr(), annot=True, fmt=".2f", cmap='coolwarm')
plt.title('Correlation Heatmap with Encoded Variables')
plt.show()
